84905,-683.8557055450854],"size":[580.7980154134148,469.4185917086162],"flags":{},"order":4,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"title":"Yumil MPM Note","properties":{"ue_properties":{"widget_ue_connectable":{},"version":"7.7","input_ue_unconnectable":{}}},"widgets_values":["## Requirements\n- Extension: comfyui-yumil-mpm\n- Application: Yumil MPM\n- Reference image\n---\n## Before You Start\n\n- If this is your first time using Yumil MPM, it is a good idea to create a sample project from the app and read at least the introductory tutorial first.\n---\n## How to Create Masks and Pose Tags\n\n1. In the Yumil Batch Save node, set `parent_folder` and `folder_name` before running the workflow. The generated files are saved to `parent_folder/folder_name`.\n2. Load a reference image into the Load Image node.\n3. Right-click the image and select Open In MaskEditor.\n4. Draw the first mask region with reasonable care.\n5. Run the workflow. The first mask is created as mask_0.\n6. Right-click the Preview Bridge for mask_1 and select Open In MaskEditor.\n7. Draw the second mask region. Areas that overlap with mask_0 are automatically excluded, so this mask can be drawn more roughly.\n8. Run the workflow again.\n9. The second mask is created as mask_1, and the remaining area is automatically created as mask_2.\n10. The workflow saves the generated text, reference image, and masks to `parent_folder/folder_name`.\n\n---\n## Notes\n\n- Set a different `folder_name` when creating files for a new image. If the same save folder is reused, existing files may be overwritten.\n"],"color":"#323","bgcolor":"#535"},{"id":17,"type":"LoadImage","pos":[-16402.25099771753,-85.71018994214059],"size":[282.798828125,314],"flags":{},"order":5,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"localized_name":"image","name":"image","type":"COMBO","widget":{"name":"image"},"link":null},{"localized_name":"choose file to upload","name":"upload","type":"IMAGEUPLOAD","widget":{"name":"upload"},"link":null}],"outputs":[{"localized_nam